title: Three Bengaluru engineering collages get bomb threat

title: Congress govt targeting Savarkar to divert public attention from MUDA 'scam': BJP
title_detail: {'type': 'text/plain', 'language': 'en-IN', 'base': 'https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/rssfeeds/-2128833038.cms', 'value': "Congress govt targeting Savarkar to divert public attention from MUDA 'scam': BJP"}
summary: Karnataka BJP president B Y Vijayendra accused the Congress government of targeting nationalist figure Vinayak Damodar Savarkar to distract from the MUDA 'scam' allegations. Vijayendra condemned the Congress' diversion tactics, while Karnataka Health Minister Dinesh Gundu Rao's remarks about Savarkar's dietary habits fueled the controversy. The incident followed an FIR against CM Siddaramaiah concerning MUDA irregularities.

title: 405 schools left with only one teacher each in Karnataka's Raichur district
title_detail: {'type': 'text/plain', 'language': 'en-IN', 'base': 'https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/rssfeeds/-2128833038.cms', 'value': "405 schools left with only one teacher each in Karnataka's Raichur district"}
summary: Raichur district faces an escalating teacher shortage crisis, exacerbated by the recent transfer of 490 teachers. This leaves 405 schools with only one permanent teacher each, severely impacting primary and high-school education. Despite promises of addressing the issue by recruiting 5,000 new teachers, no significant measures have been implemented yet.
